lines.text: [Walker shows Gene and Frog their new executive offices]
Well, boys, what do you think of it.
I'd feel a lot more at home down in the stockyard.
Well, me too. I-I don't like being cooped up. You're liable to get hydrophobia or something.
[Frog has joined the party guests at the swimming pool]
How's the water?
Why don't you find out?
It's not Saturday night.
[Gene admires the sleek airplane he and Frog will soon board]
Sure is pretty!
Ain't as pretty as horse, and when you ride a horse you don't have as far to fall.
[in order to get a free airplane ride, Patsy has convinced the airline employees that she and Gene are newlyweds]
She's such a happy little bride!
Can't I leave you alone for three minutes?
[Ann has fired Gene and Frog for causing her to miss her train]
We got back salary comin'!

[pointing to a cow]
There it is - on the hoof!
Gonna be kind of hard breakin' that into small change.
Are you sure this airplane is safe?
If it's not, you get your money back.
[Smiley tries to convince Gene that Ann's terrier is part wolf]
A wolf? The sun must have shrunk him.
[Gene and Frog are falsely arrested for rustling]
How long we in here?
They said a day for every pound that cow weighed.
I wished we'd caught a calf.
[while on a horseback ride, the chubby Frog criticizes a woman's riding technique]
You just get your weight right and you don't bounce.
How *could* you?
[Gene has just rescued a henchman from being run over by a train]
Thanks!
Don't thank me. I want you alive!
